HEADWORD: Thaumatolatry
<hw>Thau`ma*tol"a*try</hw>
<pr>(th⟦add⟧`m⟦adot⟧*t⟦ocr⟧l"⟦adot⟧*tr⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>qay^ma</grk>, <grk>qay`matos</grk>, a wonder +
<grk>latrei`a</grk> worship.]</ety> <def>Worship or undue admiration of
wonderful or miraculous things.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>thaumatolatry</qex> by which our theology has been
debased for more than a century.</q> <rj><qau>Hare.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thaumatrope</ent>⟦br⟧
